  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate, robustness gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning surrogate model trained to predict pump-induced hemolysis for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The ML surrogate replaces the full CFD solver for rapid sensitivity sweeps across component-dimension tolerances. COU1 evaluates whether the surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Validation evidence covers nominal in-distribution test-set performance only; robustness under distribution shift, measurement noise, or adversarial perturbation is noted as 'studied separately' with no linked evidence.",
