      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate inference produces bit-reproducible outputs given fixed random seed and identical input arrays across platforms.",
      "rationale": "Reproducibility tests confirm identical RH predictions (to machine precision) across three execution environments (Linux x86-64, macOS ARM, Windows x86-64) when random seeds are fixed. No iterative solver is involved; gradient-boosted tree inference is deterministic."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
