      "acceptanceCriteria": "Discretization error is not applicable to tree-based ML surrogates; acknowledgement of inapplicability is sufficient at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Gradient-boosted trees do not involve spatial or temporal discretization. The underlying CFD training data were generated with mesh-independence verified at GCI < 2% (documented in the parent CFD study). This factor is acknowledged as not directly applicable to the surrogate itself."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
