      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate output (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the COU acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device).",
      "rationale": "The surrogate is trained to predict the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) as defined in ASTM F1841. RH is the primary decision quantity for the COU. The mapping from model output to regulatory acceptance criterion is direct and unambiguous."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
