      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided for selection of gradient-boosted trees over alternative surrogate architectures; cross-validation confirms adequate fit.",
      "rationale": "Gradient-boosted trees (XGBoost) were selected after comparison with Gaussian process regression and a shallow neural network on a 20% holdout. XGBoost achieved the lowest MAPE (3.1% vs. 4.7% GP and 5.2% NN) and shortest inference time. Model form is considered appropriate for the nominal operating regime. Behavior under out-of-distribution inputs was not included in the model-form evaluation."
    },
