  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-ml-surrogate-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The ML surrogate for CPB hemolysis prediction meets all seven assessed credibility factors at or above the required level for MRL 2. Nominal test-set MAPE of 3.1% and R² of 0.971 satisfy the output comparison criterion. Six factors are not assessed, which is acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018. The assessment team acknowledges that robustness under real-world distribution shift (patient haematocrit variability, measurement noise in geometric inputs) has not been characterized in this submission; the narrative references a planned future amendment but no linked evidence is provided. This gap was not identified as a barrier to acceptance at MRL 2 given the medium model influence rating.",
